				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				SO after getting the book of darkenss I set out for Permafrost with a bounce in my step and a song in my heart.  Time to get my words and finally ditch the harvester (int is over 200 anyway... need the mana, and I hear the allure it casts is even 8 mana for 8 hp).  Anyway, I set up camp outside the icy gobbo's door and decide &quot;time to get the book&quot;.  Time turned out to be the oprative word.  It took me a hair more then 4 hours to get the book of frost.  At level 46, my pet could solo the whole jail and surrounding areas, so I cast Ignite bones just for giggles.  I took teh jailer when he spawned (only once, and only one stupid snare web).<BR>
<BR>
I was also taking the scryer and the alchemist to kill time between spawns.  1 pair of mammoth legs only.  VERANT INCREASE THE LOOT TABLES HERE AND MORE PEOPLE WILL GO.  Ahem.  Four hours later, book.  Now off to the shadow men to do my damage to them.  BTW, lots of high quality ore drops there, so get some spirit pouches or dimensional pouches!  <BR>
